 Edith Wharton, The House of Mirth\n|\nYou may control people physically by force, but you won’t change their hearts and minds—that requires trust and friendship.\n\n- Auliq-Ice\n|\nWhen we live in the love of God, we begin to pay attention to people the way God pays attention to us.\n\n- John Ortberg, Love Beyond Reason: Moving God's Love from Your Head to Your Heart\n|\nTo experience the spirit of peace, one must have freedom.Neither can be obtained without the other.\n\n- Ellen\n|\nSuccess starts with a good plan. To have it, you have to plan it.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nSay it,” I gritted out.“The High Lord of the Night Court is your mate.\n\n- Sarah J. Maas, A Court of Mist and Fury\n|\nSome people were just getting on with their lives, chatting, being young. It simply wouldn't do.\n\n- Russell\n|\nWe must, together as a nation, stop watching Fox.\n\n- Jon\n|\nOnly a philosopher's mind grows wings, since its memory always keeps it as close as possible to those realities by being close to which the gods are divine.\n\n- Plato, Phaedrus\n|\nO heavenly Father,protect and bless all thingsthat have breath: guard themfrom all evil and let them sleep in peace.\n\n- Albert\n|\nWe are like islands in the sea, separate on the surface but connected in the deep.\n\n- William\n|\nBut beauty, real beauty, ends where an intellectual expression begins. Intellect is in itself a mode of exaggeration, and destroys the harmony of any face.\n\n- Oscar Wilde, The Picture of Dorian Gray\n|\nDear Mom,I won't be home this weekend because I'm wanted for treason and I have to clear my name. Also, I took the last Sprite from the fridge.Love, Steve\n\n- Mac Barnett, The Case of the Case of Mistaken Identity\n|\nYou have to be the bravest person in the world to go out every day, being yourself when no one likes who you are.\n\n- Matthew Dicks, Memoirs of an Imaginary Friend\n|\n(On being in a position of leadership) Even if it's your dog, you've got authority over somebody. Start treating him better